title: Homogeneously Suslin set
summary: In descriptive set theory, a set S {\displaystyle S} is said to be homogeneously Suslin if it is the projection of a homogeneous tree. S {\displaystyle S} is said to be κ {\displaystyle \kappa } -homogeneously Suslin if it is the projection of a κ {\displaystyle \kappa } -homogeneous tree.
